          <div class='picture_header'>Fire Designs and Animal Mask Designs on a Jia (Wine Vessel)</div>
          Mid Shang Dynasty (15th &mdash; 13th century BCE), Shanghai Museum
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        Bronze was an important material for ceremonial vessels, such as the wine and food vessels shown below.
        The vessels played a key role in these ceremonies used for offerings to dieties and ancestors.
        The markings on the vessels had a connection with these ceremonies and the religious beliefs of the people at the time,
        especially mysterious and ferocious animals.
      </p>
