      <p>
        A <span class='bookTitle'>pou</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=25399' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'pǒu', 'a jar / pot')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>瓿</a> is an ancient vessel used for holding water or wine.
        It was in common use from the Shang to the Warring States Period.
        It is similar to a <span class='bookTitle'>zun</span> <a href='/word_detail.php?id=6611' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zūn', 'ancient wine vessel')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>尊</a> but shorter.
        <span class='bookTitle'>Pou</span> are usually round but sometimes square and have restricted opening with a wide shoulder,
        take a lid, and have a round base.
        Some have handles and some do not.
      </p>
